The paper proposes a neural network planning module that uses a novel graph convolution operator to learn and plan on irregular spatial graphs. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to machine learning, computer vision, and robotics. Specifically, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are likely categories given the focus on neural networks and learning algorithms. The use of 2D mazes and real-world street networks also suggests a potential fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.RO (Robotics). Lastly, the proposed episodic Q-learning algorithm could also make the paper relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
